value.0: Not I, my child. The text you speak of were placed there long ago by Lathander, god of the dawn, in anticipation of your coming.
The accused are confined in their towers beyond the north door. They are known as the brothers Jhareg, Karlat in the south tower and Quint within the north.
Through the north door lie stairs to the two towers. Show wisdom, Judge, and compassion for us all...
You do not have the power in this place. The castle has slipped through the weave of time. They are immortal.
As you wish. We have waited for an eternity, we can wait for another if we must.

Long have I sensed that you, too, have been trapped within this castle. The Judge has produced your written confession and found you guilty. <FirstName>, for your services as a Judge, I hope you will find this ring fitting to your firm judgement.
There is only one solution. I will take the phylactery myself. If this truly is the only way to keep Belial from the world, it is a sacrifice I must make.

Quint, you have been found innocent in the Judge's eyes. Be free from your madness and die knowing that your brother's soul shall not be tainted by undeath. <FirstName>, for your services as a Judge, I hope you will find this amulet fitting to your willful judgement.

Karlat, you have been found innocent in the Judge's eyes. Here is the phylactery stolen from you by your brother. Take it and go. <FirstName>, for your services as a Judge, I hope you will find these boots fitting to your swift judgement.
May the Judge always know the blessings of the Morninglord.
<StartCheck>[Insight]</Start> Did you write the text on those signs?
